FBIS4-34919 "drlat123_c_94012" FBIS-LAT-94-123 Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 MEXICO New Chiapas Peace Commissioner Meets Media New Chiapas Peace Commissioner Meets Media PA2406172294 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network in Spanish 1300 GMT 24 Jun 94 PA2406172294 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network in Spanish 1300 GMT 24 Jun 94 Spanish BFN [Report on news conference by Jorge Madrazo Cuellar, the newly appointed commissioner for peace and reconciliation in Chiapas, with unidentified reporters in Mexico City on 23 June; from the "Early Morning" newscast -- recorded] [Text] [Madrazo Cuellar] I have asked the Human Rights Commission's Council to report on my appointment and my formal request to the Senate for a temporary leave of absence as president of the National Human Rights Commission. Once the Senate and the Human Rights Commission finalizes this, I will be ready to answer your many questions, my journalist friends. I can tell you that to this important and difficult task I will commit all of my abilities and eagerness to legally serve Mexico and the president of the republic. I am asking you to be understanding. I hope that as soon as the legal procedures are completed, you and I will be able to meet in order that I can answer your questions. [Reporter] Any conditions for resuming the talks? [Madrazo Cuellar] Again, I am asking you to be understanding and let the procedures be completed to enable me to legally and respectfully answer questions from the media. [Reporter] [Words indistinct] [Madrazo Cuellar] Tomorrow morning. [Reporter] [Words indistinct] [Madrazo Cuellar] The National Commission. As soon as the request for the absence of leave is cleared, the office will be managed by Carlos Dominguez. Thank you.
